{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/instalar-ruby-on-rails-macos/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>En este tutorial configuraremos un entorno de desarrollo Ruby on Rails en macOS 10.14 Mojave.</p>\n<h2 id=\"instalando-homebrew\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#instalando-homebrew\" aria-label=\"instalando homebrew permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Instalando Homebrew</h2>\n<p>Lo primero que debemos tener instalado Homebrew, lo cual ya explicamos anteriormente <a href=\"/syntax-highlighting-nano/#instalar-homebrew\">aqu√≠</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"instalando-ruby\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#instalando-ruby\" aria-label=\"instalando ruby permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Instalando Ruby</h2>\n<p>Ahora que tenemos instalado Homebrew, podemos usarlo para instalar Ruby.</p>\n<p>Vamos a usar <a href=\"https://github.com/sstephenson/rbenv\">rbenv</a> para instalar y administrar nuestras versiones de Ruby.</p>\n<p>Para hacer esto, ejecuta los siguientes comandos en tu Terminal:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span>brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> rbenv ruby-build\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Agrega rbenv a bash para que se cargue cada vez que abra una terminal</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">'if which rbenv > /dev/null; then eval \"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>rbenv init -<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"; fi'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">>></span> ~/.bash_profile\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">source</span> ~/.bash_profile\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># O si tienes zsh</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">'if which rbenv > /dev/null; then eval \"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span>rbenv init -<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"; fi'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">>></span> ~/.zshrc\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">source</span> ~/.zshrc\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Instalar Ruby</span>\nrbenv <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token number\">2.6</span>.3\nrbenv global <span class=\"token number\">2.6</span>.3\nruby -v</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"instalando-rails\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#instalando-rails\" aria-label=\"instalando rails permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Instalando Rails</h2>\n<p>Instalar Rails es tan simple como ejecutar el siguiente comando en la Terminal:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span>gem <span class=\"token function\">install</span> rails -v <span class=\"token number\">6.0</span>.0.rc1</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Rails ahora est√° instalado, pero para que podamos usar el ejecutable de rails, necesitamos decirle a rbenv que lo vea:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"\u001ebash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-\u001ebash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-\u001ebash\">rbenv rehash</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Y ahora podemos verificar que Rails est√° instalado:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span>rails -v\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Rails 6.0.0.rc1</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"configurar-una-base-de-datos\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#configurar-una-base-de-datos\" aria-label=\"configurar una base de datos permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Configurar una base de datos</h2>\n<p>Vamos a instalar sqlite3 desde homebrew porque no podemos usar la versi√≥n integrada con macOS sin tener algunos problemas.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span>brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> sqlite3</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Rails usa sqlite3 como la base de datos predeterminada. Lo m√°s probable es que no quierasusarlo porque est√° almacenado como un archivo simple en el disco. Probablemente quieras algo m√°s robusto como MySQL o PostgreSQL.</p>\n<p>Hay mucha documentaci√≥n sobre ambos, por lo que puede elegir uno con el que se sienta m√°s c√≥modo. Si viene de PHP, es posible que ya est√© familiarizado con MySQL. Si eres nuevo en las bases de datos, te sugiero que saltes a <a href=\"#postgresql\">configurar PostgreSQL</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"mysql\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mysql\" aria-label=\"mysql permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>MySQL</h3>\n<p>Puedes instalar el servidor <a href=\"http://www.mysql.com/\">MySQL</a> y el cliente desde Homebrew:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span>brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> mysql</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Una vez que este comando haya terminado, le da un par de comandos para ejecutar. Siga las instrucciones y ejec√∫telas:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span><span class=\"token comment\"># mysql se ejecutar√° al iniciar sesi√≥n:</span>\nbrew services start mysql</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Por defecto, el usuario mysql es <code class=\"language-text\">root</code> sin contrase√±a. Cuando haya terminado, puede saltar a los <a href=\"#pasos-finales\">Pasos finales</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"postgresql\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#postgresql\" aria-label=\"postgresql permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>PostgreSQL</h3>\n<p>Puedes instalar el servidor y el cliente de <a href=\"http://www.postgresql.org/\">PostgreSQL</a> desde Homebrew:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span>brew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> postgresql</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Una vez que este comando haya terminado, le da un par de comandos para ejecutar. Siga las instrucciones y ejec√∫telas:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span><span class=\"token comment\"># postgresql se ejecutar√° al iniciar sesi√≥n:</span>\nbrew services start postgresql</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Por defecto, el usuario postgresql es su nombre de usuario OS X actual sin contrase√±a. Por ejemplo, mi usuario de OS X es <code class=\"language-text\">lavaldi</code>, por lo que puedo iniciar sesi√≥n en postgresql con ese nombre de usuario.</p>\n<h2 id=\"pasos-finales\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pasos-finales\" aria-label=\"pasos finales permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pasos finales</h2>\n<p>Mojave cambi√≥ la ubicaci√≥n de los archivos de encabezado necesarios para compilar extensiones C. Es posible que debas ejecutar el siguiente comando para instalar pg u otras gemas que requieren extensiones C:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> installer -pkg /Library/Developer/CommandLineTools/Packages/macOS_SDK_headers_for_macOS_10.14.pkg -target /</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Y ahora, el momento de la verdad. Creemos su primera aplicaci√≥n Rails:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-bash line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"command-line-prompt\"><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span><span data-user=root data-host=localhost></span></span>rails new myapp\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">#### Si usas MySQL</span>\nrails new myapp -d mysql\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">#### Si usas Postgres</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Ten en cuenta que deber√°s cambiar el nombre de usuario en config/database.yml para que sea</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># el mismo que su cuenta de usuario OSX. (por ejemplo, el m√≠o es 'lavaldi')</span>\nrails new myapp -d postgresql\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Ingresa al directorio de la aplicaci√≥n</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> myapp\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Si configura MySQL o Postgres con un nombre de usuario/contrase√±a, modifique el</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># archivo config/database.yml para que contenga el nombre de usuario/contrase√±a que especific√≥</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Crear la BD</span>\nrake db:create\n\nrails server</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>¬°Ahora puedes ir a <a href=\"http://localhost:3000\">http://localhost:3000</a> para ver tu nuevo sitio web!</p>\n<p>Ahora que tienes la configuraci√≥n de tu m√°quina, es hora de comenzar a construir algunas aplicaciones Rails.</p>\n<p>Si recibiste un error que dec√≠a <code class=\"language-text\">Access denied for user &#39;root&#39;@&#39;localhost&#39; (using password: NO)</code>, entonces necesitas actualizar el archivo <code class=\"language-text\">config/database.yml</code> para que coincida con el nombre de usuario y la contrase√±a de la base de datos üòâ</p>","excerpt":"En este tutorial configuraremos un entorno de desarrollo Ruby on Rails en macOS 10.14 Mojave. Instalando Homebrew Lo primero que debemos‚Ä¶","fields":{"slug":"/instalar-ruby-on-rails-macos/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Instalar Ruby on Rails en MacOS","date":"August 15, 2019","tags":["macOS","ruby","ruby on rails","rbenv"],"description":null,"banner":null,"slug":"instalar-ruby-on-rails-macos"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/instalar-ruby-on-rails-macos/","previous":{"id":"ce772390-9b20-5984-be9b-a3e1719d01ca","frontmatter":{"title":"egghead.io: favorite JavaScript resources","banner":null,"categories":["Code"],"tags":["learn","JavaScript","resources"],"template":"post"},"fields":{"slug":"/javascript-resources/"}},"next":{"id":"777ba76f-d570-5ec2-9622-35d700520ffa","frontmatter":{"title":"Eliminar archivos del historial de git","banner":null,"categories":["Code"],"tags":["git"],"template":"post"},"fields":{"slug":"/como-eliminar-archivos-completamente-historial-git/"}},"coverPicture":"./public/a21de5ffde075472db25d5f6b9ec46f0.png"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}